cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques applied to image understanding. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a learning strategy that involves extracting object-part concepts from a pre-trained convolutional neural network (CNN), which falls under the category of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also deals with semantic understanding of images, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper uses a four-layer And-Or graph to organize the mined latent patterns, which is a technique used in neural networks. Hence, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a likely category.
